Gauteng Education MEC Panyaza Lesufi updates parents of Parktown Boys’ High School on the latest developments regarding the Enock Mpianzi matter. The school has been under pressure following the death of 13-year-old Mpianzi at an orientation camp in Brits. On Wednesday, Lesufi said he will be acting against Parktown Boys’ High School within 48 hours. Lesufi said information that shows possible negligence by the school has emerged. 